## Important Rules

- Passwords: bcrypt-hashed in `password` field ‚Äî never store plain text
- Roles: `admin` or `customer` (default) ‚Äî enforce in middlewares
- Error strings drive HTTP status (e.g. "Email already in use" ‚Üí 409)
- Collections: default names (users, dishes, packages)
- **Business logic in services only** ‚Äî controllers stay thin
- **Schema changes:** update model + corresponding service methods
- **New middleware:** place in `middlewares/`, mount in `app.js` or route file

## When Modifying Code

| Change | Location |
|--------|----------|
| Validation rules | `validations/` |
| Business logic | `services/` (never controllers) |
| New routes | Follow existing middleware pattern |
| DB schema | `models/` + update services |
| New middleware | `middlewares/` + document purpose |
